      "date": "2011-05-04 01:49:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHi Andreas,\nThe issue still exists:\n\n[root@fat-intel-4 ~]# mkfs.lustre --mgs --mdt --backfstype=ext3 --device-size=2000000 --reformat --verbose /dev/sdb\n\n   Permanent disk data:\nTarget:     lustre-MDTffff\nIndex:      unassigned\nLustre FS:  lustre\nMount type: ext3\nFlags:      0x75\n              (MDT MGS needs_index first_time update )\nPersistent mount opts: user_xattr,errors=remount-ro\nParameters:\n\ndevice size = 239429MB\nformatting backing filesystem ext3 on /dev/sdb\n        target name  lustre-MDTffff\n        4k blocks     500000\n        options        -J size=76 -I 512 -i 2048 -O dirdata,uninit_bg,dir_nlink,huge_file,flex_bg -E lazy_journal_init, -F\nmkfs_cmd = mke2fs -j -b 4096 -L lustre-MDTffff  -J size=76 -I 512 -i 2048 -O dirdata,uninit_bg,dir_nlink,huge_file,flex_bg -E lazy_journal_init, -F /dev/sdb 500000\ncmd: mke2fs -j -b 4096 -L lustre-MDTffff  -J size=76 -I 512 -i 2048 -O dirdata,uninit_bg,dir_nlink,huge_file,flex_bg -E lazy_journal_init, -F /dev/sdb 500000\nmke2fs 1.41.14.wc1 (20-Jan-2011)\nFilesystem label=lustre-MDTffff\nOS type: Linux\nBlock size=4096 (log=2)\nFragment size=4096 (log=2)\nStride=0 blocks, Stripe width=0 blocks\n1000184 inodes, 500000 blocks\n25000 blocks (5.00%) reserved for the super user\nFirst data block=0\nMaximum filesystem blocks=514086912\n31 block groups\n16528 blocks per group, 16528 fragments per group\n32264 inodes per group\nSuperblock backups stored on blocks:\n        16528, 49584, 82640, 115696, 148752, 413200, 446256\n\nWriting inode tables: done\nCreating journal (19456 blocks): done\nWriting superblocks and filesystem accounting information: done\n\nThis filesystem will be automatically checked every 36 mounts or\n180 days, whichever comes first.  Use tune2fs -c or -i to override.\nmkfs.lustre: Unable to mount /dev/sdb: Invalid argument\n\nmkfs.lustre FATAL: failed to write local files\nmkfs.lustre: exiting with 22 (Invalid argument)\n\n[root@fat-intel-4 ~]# dmesg\nEXT3-fs: sdb: couldn't mount because of unsupported optional features (1200).",
